objectives.name: Primary Safety Objective (All Cohorts)
objectives.text: To describe the safety profile of 20vPnC in adults 18 years of age and older.

objectives.name: Primary Immunogenicity Objective 1 - Cohort 1
objectives.text: To demonstrate that the immune responses to the 13 serotypes in 13vPnC (1, 3, 4, 5, 6A, 6B, 7F, 9V, 14, 18C, 19A, 19F, and 23F) induced by 20vPnC in adults 60 years of age and older are noninferior to the immune response induced by 13vPnC.

objectives.name: Primary Immunogenicity Objective 2 - Cohort 1
objectives.text: To demonstrate that the immune responses to the 7 additional serotypes (8, 10A, 11A, 12F, 15B, 22F, and 33F) induced by 20vPnC in adults 60 years of age and older are noninferior to the immune response induced by PPSV23.

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - Cohort 2
objectives.text: To demonstrate that the immune responses to the 20 serotypes in 20vPnC induced in adults 50 through 59 years of age are noninferior to the immune responses induced by 20vPnC in adults 60 through 64 years of age.

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - Cohort 3
objectives.text: To demonstrate that the immune responses to the 20 serotypes in 20vPnC induced in adults 18 through 49 years of age are noninferior to the immune responses induced by 20vPnC in adults 60 through 64 years of age.

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - All Cohorts
objectives.text: To describe the immune responses to 20vPnC in adults 60 years of age and older, 50 through 59 years of age, and 18 through 49 years of age.

endpoints.name: Prompted Local Reactions
endpoints.text: Reported prompted local reactions (redness, swelling, and pain at the injection site) within 10 days after vaccination.

endpoints.name: Prompted Systemic Events
endpoints.text: Reported prompted systemic events (fever, headache, fatigue, muscle pain, and joint pain) within 7 days after vaccination.

endpoints.name: Adverse Events
endpoints.text: Reported adverse events (AEs) within 1 month after vaccination.

endpoints.name: SAEs and NDCMCs
endpoints.text: Reported serious adverse events (SAEs) and newly diagnosed chronic medical conditions (NDCMCs) within 6 months after vaccination.

endpoints.name: Primary Immunogenicity Endpoint - Cohort 1
endpoints.text: Serotype-specific opsonophagocytic activity (OPA) titers 1 month after vaccination.

endpoints.name: Secondary Endpoint - Cohort 2
endpoints.text: Serotype-specific OPA titers 1 month after vaccination.

endpoints.name: Secondary Endpoint - Cohort 3
endpoints.text: Serotype-specific OPA titers 1 month after vaccination.

endpoints.name: OPA Fold Rise
endpoints.text: Fold rise in serotype-specific OPA titers from before to 1 month after vaccination.

endpoints.name: >=4-Fold OPA Rise
endpoints.text: >=4-Fold rise in serotype-specific OPA titers from before to 1 month after vaccination.

endpoints.name: OPA >=LLOQ
endpoints.text: Serotype-specific OPA titers greater than or equal to the lower limit of quantitation (>=LLOQ) 1 month after vaccination.

estimands.name: Primary Immunogenicity Estimand - Cohort 1
estimands.populationSummary: Adults 60 years of age and older with no history of pneumococcal vaccination (Cohort 1) Summary measure: Geometric mean ratio (GMR).

intercurrentEvents.name: Protocol deviation
intercurrentEvents.text: Major protocol deviations affecting the immunogenicity assessment

intercurrentEvents.name: Non-study vaccination
intercurrentEvents.text: Receipt of prohibited non-study pneumococcal vaccines

intercurrentEvents.name: Withdrawal/Discontinuation
intercurrentEvents.text: Subject withdraws from study before the 1-month blood draw

estimands.variableOfInterest: Serotype-specific opsonophagocytic activity (OPA) titers 1 month after vaccination

estimands.name: Primary Safety Estimand - Local Reactions
estimands.populationSummary: Adults 18 years of age and older (All Cohorts) Summary measure: Percentage of subjects.

intercurrentEvents.name: Treatment discontinuation
intercurrentEvents.text: Subject discontinues study before the 10-day diary period is complete

estimands.analysisPopulation: Adults 18 years of age and older (All Cohorts)
estimands.variableOfInterest: Reported prompted local reactions within 10 days

estimands.populationSummary: Adults 50 through 59 years of age (Cohort 2) compared to adults 60 through 64 years of age Summary measure: Geometric mean ratio (GMR).

intercurrentEvents.text: Missing immunogenicity data at the 1-month visit

estimands.analysisPopulation: Adults 50 through 59 years of age (Cohort 2) compared to adults 60 through 64 years of age
